headline: Starbucks Teams With AI Startup NomadGo To Automate Counting In 11,000 Stores — CTO Says Goodbye To Manual Tallies Forever
summary: Starbucks (NASDAQ:SBUX) just revolutionized how coffee gets counted. The Seattle coffee giant announced Sept. 3 it has partnered with NomadGo to deploy AI-powered automated counting across all 11,000 North American company-operated stores by September’s end. The transformation at Starbucks represents a massive shift from manual inventory tallies to instant, accurate counts using nothing more than a handheld tablet. headline: Carlyle, EQT, HongShan among final bidders for Starbucks China, sources say
summary: Global investment firms Carlyle Group and EQT, alongside regional players HongShan Capital Group and Boyu Capital, are preparing final offers for a controlling stake in Starbucks' China operations, said five people with knowledge of the matter.  Starbucks has asked them to submit binding bids by early October, said three of the sources, who declined to be identified as the information was private.  Starbucks had invited about 10 potential buyers to submit non-binding bids by early September, with most offering to value the China business at as much as $5 billion, Reuters reported last month.
